test module¶

test.print_multiply(x, y)[source]¶

print the product of two numbers This function takes two numbers and prints the product of them. The multiplication is done using the built-in function ‘*’.

x: the first number y: the second number

>>> print_multiply(1, 2)
2
>>> print_multiply(-1, 2)
-2
test.print_sum(x, y)[source]¶

print the sum of two numbers This function takes two numbers and prints the sum of them. The addition is done using the built-in function ‘+’.

x: the first number y: the second number

>>> print_sum(1, 2)
3
>>> print_sum(-1, 2)
1
